cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Kipp: Oracle-Gated, Placement-Invariant Paged Attention for Verifiable LLM Inference"
message: "If you use Kipp in academic work, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "Khachatryan Johansson"
    given-names: "David"
    email: david@cortify.io
repository-code: "https://github.com/Polished-Snow/Kipp"
abstract: >-
  Kipp is a hand-written C11 inference engine for the pinned Qwen3 dense
  model family, with a scalar CPU correctness oracle and correctness-gated
  Apple Metal and NVIDIA CUDA backends. Its paged key-value cache is
  permutation-invariant: the physical placement of KV blocks is arbitrary,
  so a sequence's output is bitwise-identical under any permutation of its
  block table. This property is used as a continuous correctness contract
  for verifiable, deterministic LLM inference.
keywords:
  - large language models
  - inference engine
  - paged attention
  - KV cache
  - deterministic inference
  - verifiable systems
  - Qwen3
license: MIT
version: 0.0.3
